  - data quality issues


✅ Key Observability Areas in MLOps
🔷 1. Data Observability (Input Monitoring)
✅ What we track
Data drift (input distribution change)
Missing values
Schema changes
Feature anomalies


✅ Example
Training:
age range: 20–60

Production:
age range: 10–90 ❌

👉 Model accuracy drops
✅ With Dynatrace
Custom metrics via API
Logs ingestion for data validation
Alerts on anomalies


🔷 2. Model Performance Metrics
✅ Core ML Metrics
Accuracy
Precision
Recall
F1-score


✅ In production (important)
Prediction confidence
Error rate
Model drift

✅ Example
Accuracy: 92% → drops to 75% ❌

👉 Dynatrace triggers alert

🔷 3. Prediction Monitoring
✅ What we track
Number of predictions
Latency per prediction
Failed predictions


✅ Example metrics
Requests/sec
Response time
Error %


✅ Dynatrace strength 💪
Dynatrace automatically tracks:
Service → API → Request latency → Failures


🔷 4. Infrastructure Observability

✅ What we monitor
CPU usage
Memory usage
Pod health (Kubernetes / KServe)
GPU usage (if used)


✅ Dynatrace gives:
Full stack monitoring ✅
Auto-detection of containers ✅
Kubernetes insights ✅


✅ Example alert
CPU > 85% → scale up
Memory leak → restart pod

🔷 5. Model Drift Detection
✅ Types
Data drift ✅
Concept drift ✅


✅ What happens
Training data ≠ Production data

👉 Accuracy drops silently ❌
✅ Dynatrace usage

Custom metrics for feature distributions
Alerts using thresholds / AI engine (Davis AI)
